f:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Hyperliquid calculates funding rates every hour using on-chain mark price and index price data, with all computations verifiable on their L1 blockchain. The funding rate reflects the premium or discount between FTM perpetual price and spot reference, updated continuously through the order book mechanism. Since all trades settle on-chain with USDC margin, funding payments are automatically processed without counterparty risk. The 1-hour frequency creates more granular arbitrage opportunities compared to traditional 8-hour cycles on centralized exchanges."}]
10:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","FTM","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"FTM exhibits significant funding rate volatility due to its mid-tier market cap and correlation with DeFi trends, creating profitable arbitrage windows. The Fantom ecosystem's focus on DeFi applications often drives speculative interest, leading to funding rate premiums during bull runs and discounts during corrections. Hyperliquid's on-chain transparency allows traders to verify funding calculations and predict rate changes more accurately than on CEXs."}]]}]
11:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical FTM Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"FTM funding rates on Hyperliquid have shown distinct patterns correlating with Fantom ecosystem developments and broader L1 narratives. During periods of DeFi activity on Fantom, funding rates typically turn positive as long positions accumulate, reaching peaks of 0.05-0.15% hourly during major announcements. Conversely, during market downturns or when competing L1s gain attention, FTM often trades at negative funding rates of -0.02% to -0.08% hourly. The 1-hour funding cycle on Hyperliquid captures these sentiment shifts more precisely than traditional exchanges, creating multiple daily arbitrage opportunities. Historical data shows FTM funding rates are most volatile during European and US trading hours when DeFi activity peaks."}]]}]
12:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities and Strategies"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"The combination of Hyperliquid's hourly funding and FTM's volatility creates systematic arbitrage opportunities against CEXs with 8-hour cycles. Traders can exploit funding rate differentials by shorting FTM on Hyperliquid during high positive rates while longing on exchanges like Binance or OKX. The on-chain settlement eliminates counterparty risk while USDC margins simplify cross-platform hedging calculations. Advanced strategies involve monitoring Fantom on-chain metrics to predict funding direction changes, as TVL fluctuations and DEX volumes often precede perpetual funding shifts. The lack of KYC requirements enables rapid strategy deployment for institutional arbitrageurs."}]]}]
13:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations and Mitigation"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"While Hyperliquid's on-chain architecture reduces operational risks, traders face unique challenges including potential network congestion during high volatility periods. The single-chain ecosystem means no cross-chain redundancy if technical issues arise, though the platform's sub-second finality typically maintains performance. USDC-only margins require careful consideration of stablecoin depeg risks, particularly during broader crypto market stress. Position sizing should account for FTM's mid-cap volatility, as 20-30% daily moves can quickly erode funding arbitrage profits if not properly hedged. The newer platform's limited track record compared to established CEXs warrants conservative initial exposure until operational resilience is proven over multiple market cycles."}]]}]
14:["$","$L16",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often are FTM funding rates updated on Hyperliquid?","answer":"Funding rates are calculated and applied every hour on Hyperliquid, providing 24 funding payments per day compared to 3 on most CEXs. This creates more frequent arbitrage opportunities but requires active monitoring of position costs."},{"question":"Can I verify FTM funding rate calculations on-chain?","answer":"Yes, all funding rate calculations are transparent and verifiable on Hyperliquid's L1 blockchain. You can audit the mark price, index price, and interest rate components that determine the final funding rate for each hourly period."},{"question":"What are typical FTM funding rates during market volatility?","answer":"During high volatility, FTM funding rates can range from -0.1% to +0.2% hourly on Hyperliquid. Bull market conditions often see sustained positive rates of 0.05-0.15% hourly, while bear markets may show negative rates of -0.03% to -0.08% hourly."},{"question":"Is there slippage risk when arbitraging FTM funding on Hyperliquid?","answer":"The on-chain order book provides transparent pricing, but FTM's mid-tier liquidity means larger positions may experience slippage during volatile periods. The platform's sub-second finality helps minimize execution delays compared to traditional blockchain-based DEXs."}]}]
